WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.240
è un termine che è linkato a Beliabon, o in Germania a amore,

00:06.520 --> 00:16.340
che è per dire che qualcuno che crede, amora o pregge la loro allogia o la loro allogia

00:16.340 --> 00:21.000
o l'allegio o la loro allogia a Dio o a Dio.

00:21.820 --> 00:25.640
Questo è quello che il religioso ha significato in un momento.

00:25.640 --> 00:31.140
Ma nel XVI-XVI secolo, il religioso è diventato un pronome abstratto,

00:31.700 --> 00:32.700
invece di un esattivo,

00:33.780 --> 00:41.660
e ha iniziato a riferire a un sistema intero di pratiche

00:41.660 --> 00:46.280
che contengono una comunità, non solo quella,

00:46.540 --> 00:51.880
ma una comunità che ha un set di doctrini coerenti

00:51.880 --> 00:53.960
e che ha una struttura istituzionale.

00:54.960 --> 00:56.860
E il religioso,

00:57.220 --> 01:05.020
quindi, invece di il religioso essere una proprietà di uomini o di gruppi di uomini,

01:05.800 --> 01:09.200
i uomini erano una proprietà di religioso.

01:09.740 --> 01:13.520
I uomini iniziarono a sopravviare alla religiosa.

01:14.460 --> 01:21.200
E penso che questo sia stato, in un senso,

01:22.000 --> 01:24.720
invece di sopravviare a Dio o a Dio,

01:24.940 --> 01:28.760
o avere alcune relazioni con Dio o Dio,

01:28.960 --> 01:33.340
le persone iniziarono a vedere in relazione a questa comunità

01:34.960 --> 01:37.660
istituzionale e strutturata.

01:38.640 --> 01:43.780
E puoi capire come l'uomo iniziò a cambiare

01:43.780 --> 01:47.120
e questa idea di identità,

01:47.300 --> 01:49.400
che è un'identità categorica,

01:50.200 --> 01:52.660
che è un'identità strutturata,

01:53.720 --> 01:54.580
iniziava ad essere nata.

01:54.680 --> 01:59.660
E penso che dobbiamo tornare a questo periodo moderno

02:00.200 --> 02:01.680
in modo da capire

02:02.680 --> 02:03.500
dove,

02:04.360 --> 02:07.420
la roots di alcuni di questi problemi

02:07.420 --> 02:08.400
sono.

02:08.880 --> 02:10.480
Poi immaginiamo

02:10.480 --> 02:11.500
cosa succederà

02:11.500 --> 02:13.400
se, per esempio,

02:13.400 --> 02:19.960
le persone che

02:19.960 --> 02:22.020
imparano molto da

02:22.260 --> 02:28.040
Hume, Locke, Berkley, Kant, Hegel, Marx, Spinoza,

02:28.040 --> 02:30.400
inizieranno a chiamarsi

02:30.400 --> 02:34.780
Hume, Locke, Kant, Hegel,

02:36.240 --> 02:36.860
e

02:36.860 --> 02:40.840
se inizieranno a pensare a loro

02:40.840 --> 02:45.880
come una comunità e un'associazione strutturata

02:45.880 --> 02:50.040
di Kant, che crede solo a Kant e a nessuno altro,

02:51.480 --> 02:54.140
la kind of intellectual disagreement

02:54.140 --> 02:57.000
che vediamo nella filosofia

02:58.340 --> 03:03.340
tornerà a majori conflitti ideologici e politici

03:03.340 --> 03:07.000
e magari i filosofi saranno ancora violenti

03:07.520 --> 03:08.840
ad uno l'altro, chi lo sa.

03:09.600 --> 03:09.620
Ma,

03:11.480 --> 03:13.080
penso che questo

03:13.080 --> 03:15.660
intero sistema deve essere

03:15.660 --> 03:16.700
smantellato.

03:18.620 --> 03:21.660
E l'altra cosa, ovviamente, la distinzione musicale che ho detto,

03:21.920 --> 03:23.000
questo è qualcosa che,

03:23.800 --> 03:26.160
se lo introdurete in questa notione di religione,

03:26.160 --> 03:28.460
la distinzione musicale

03:28.460 --> 03:31.460
racconta la distinzione

03:31.460 --> 03:33.480
tra la vera religione

03:33.480 --> 03:35.160
e la falsa religione.

03:35.900 --> 03:37.360
L'idea che,

03:37.360 --> 03:41.520
non è solo l'idea che c'è solo un Dio,

03:41.960 --> 03:43.420
che è qualcosa che è comune

03:43.420 --> 03:45.800
a molte, molte religioni,

03:45.920 --> 03:48.260
non solo a certe religioni,

03:48.500 --> 03:50.180
ma l'idea che c'è

03:51.560 --> 03:53.140
un vero Dio

03:53.140 --> 03:55.160
e tutti gli altri Dio sono falsi

03:55.160 --> 03:56.600
e, per questo,

03:56.840 --> 03:59.160
dovrebbero essere esclusi

04:00.420 --> 04:01.580
o hanno

04:01.580 --> 04:02.760
un'idea esclusiva

04:02.760 --> 04:03.660
a un Dio,

04:03.720 --> 04:06.460
invece di tutti gli altri falsi Dio.

04:07.000 --> 04:09.400
Penso che sia anche

04:09.400 --> 04:11.080
un'idea che ha

04:11.080 --> 04:12.980
giocato il havoc.

04:14.900 --> 04:15.520
Se lo guardate,

04:16.880 --> 04:18.320
siamo qui

04:18.940 --> 04:20.540
parlando del pluralismo,

04:20.720 --> 04:22.860
ma questo è un monismo esclusivo.

04:22.860 --> 04:25.340
Penso che

04:25.340 --> 04:25.820
abbia

04:25.820 --> 04:27.120
un'impatto

04:27.120 --> 04:30.000
molto dimenticato

04:30.380 --> 04:31.260
sul modo in cui

04:31.260 --> 04:33.220
le persone si rilassano.

04:35.300 --> 04:36.380
Quindi,

04:36.380 --> 04:38.700
l'idea che

04:38.700 --> 04:39.700
la religione è una cosa,

04:39.780 --> 04:42.520
devi scegliere una religione

04:42.520 --> 04:44.960
all'esclusione di ogni altra religione,

04:45.540 --> 04:46.620
che è

04:46.620 --> 04:48.860
introdotta nel discorso

04:48.860 --> 04:50.920
da una distinzione musicale.

04:50.920 --> 04:52.460
Penso che questo sia

04:52.460 --> 04:54.920
una cosa che dobbiamo domandare

04:54.920 --> 04:55.820
e scegliere.

04:57.380 --> 04:58.180
Volevo solo

04:58.640 --> 05:00.920
mettere su la tavola

05:01.900 --> 05:02.920
questa molto veloce

05:05.040 --> 05:05.800
radicalizzazione

05:05.800 --> 05:07.100
di

05:07.100 --> 05:08.820
la fiducia e delle identità

05:08.820 --> 05:10.900
che si sono fatti nel XV-XVI secolo,

05:11.380 --> 05:13.000
che continua ad avere un impatto

05:13.000 --> 05:14.080
su noi oggi

05:14.080 --> 05:15.940
e che è

05:15.940 --> 05:19.200
ora totalmente globale.

05:19.200 --> 05:21.320
Non c'è una sola

05:22.540 --> 05:23.260
persona

05:23.260 --> 05:23.960
che si chiama

05:25.980 --> 05:26.700
religione

05:27.440 --> 05:29.340
nella maggior parte del mondo

05:29.340 --> 05:30.400
che non pensa

05:30.400 --> 05:32.820
nella sua o la sua religione in questo modo.

05:33.080 --> 05:34.360
Penso che sia il momento

05:34.360 --> 05:36.160
che, intellettualmente, la prendiamo seriamente

05:36.160 --> 05:37.200
e iniziamo a scegliere.

05:37.980 --> 05:39.560
Thank you.

05:40.420 --> 05:41.140
Sebastiano.

05:42.720 --> 05:45.660
Before I start, let me thank

05:45.660 --> 05:47.680
Rosette Dialogue of Civilization.

05:47.680 --> 05:49.740
I'm informed of the project

05:49.740 --> 05:52.160
since the beginning and I always thought it was great

05:52.160 --> 05:53.980
but I can say it's still better

05:53.980 --> 05:55.560
also because it's a beautiful day

05:55.560 --> 05:57.560
in this fantastic foundation, of course.

05:57.920 --> 05:59.880
But I think it's very important that we discuss

05:59.880 --> 06:01.700
these things among us and

06:01.700 --> 06:03.520
try to understand as much as we can

06:03.520 --> 06:06.060
on such a difficult and complex subject.

06:06.920 --> 06:07.890
I mean, today we are

06:08.420 --> 06:09.580
supposed to speak about

06:09.580 --> 06:11.960
global challenges

06:11.960 --> 06:12.880
for politics

06:13.800 --> 06:16.180
within the framework of the radicalization

06:16.180 --> 06:18.400
of identity. The first thing I note

06:18.400 --> 06:20.020
is that

06:20.020 --> 06:21.780
usually we think of global changes

06:21.780 --> 06:23.460
in very different terms.

06:24.380 --> 06:26.180
Global changes usually derive

06:26.180 --> 06:28.280
from more or less universal

06:28.280 --> 06:30.180
problems confronted with

06:30.940 --> 06:32.260
local institution.

06:33.440 --> 06:34.180
For instance,

06:34.880 --> 06:35.560
take environment.

06:37.020 --> 06:38.120
You cannot solve

06:38.120 --> 06:39.880
problems of environment in one country.

06:40.160 --> 06:42.180
You need to expand them

06:42.940 --> 06:44.400
more or less universally.

06:44.400 --> 06:46.400
That's why you have

06:47.000 --> 06:48.080
a global challenge

06:48.080 --> 06:50.200
because the problem is global.

06:50.960 --> 06:52.360
The institutions you have are not global.

06:52.420 --> 06:54.760
They are local and you cannot solve the problem

06:54.760 --> 06:55.880
given this gap.

06:57.520 --> 06:58.680
So the same can be

06:58.680 --> 06:59.460
said for finance.

07:00.200 --> 07:02.400
You need regulation. This regulation cannot be

07:02.960 --> 07:04.780
only local. They must be

07:04.780 --> 07:06.620
general. And there are

07:06.620 --> 07:08.640
not such institutions

07:08.640 --> 07:09.640
that can do that.

07:10.040 --> 07:12.340
So the structure of global challenging

07:12.340 --> 07:14.580
for politics usually is

07:14.580 --> 07:15.880
global problems

07:15.880 --> 07:18.000
too much local

07:18.000 --> 07:20.380
institutions. Instead when we speak

07:20.380 --> 07:22.260
of radical identities, perhaps

07:22.260 --> 07:23.920
we have an opposite problem.

07:24.400 --> 07:26.700
Institutional is too large, too big,

07:27.160 --> 07:27.800
too comprehensive

07:28.340 --> 07:30.200
and we need something more specific,

07:30.660 --> 07:32.040
more local.

07:33.540 --> 07:34.520
And so we have

07:34.520 --> 07:36.660
a kind of reversion.

07:37.160 --> 07:38.460
The problem is the other way round.

07:38.960 --> 07:40.580
Instead of having global

07:40.580 --> 07:42.520
problems and local institutions, we have

07:42.520 --> 07:44.580
local problems and institutions that

07:44.580 --> 07:45.300
are too large.

07:46.240 --> 07:48.820
How to confront ourselves with

07:48.820 --> 07:50.000
such kind of problems?

07:50.800 --> 07:52.240
Within political philosophy,

07:52.640 --> 07:53.680
am I not so radical?

07:54.160 --> 07:55.840
I think of myself as a moderate

07:56.580 --> 07:58.220
Kantian, so Rajiv don't worry,

07:58.260 --> 08:00.800
we will not be too dangerous.

08:02.580 --> 08:04.280
There are two main solutions I see.

08:04.420 --> 08:06.360
One is Kimlik as

08:06.360 --> 08:08.880
liberal multiculturalism.

08:08.880 --> 08:11.020
As Vivorca said before,

08:11.220 --> 08:13.180
is not exactly popular in this moment

08:13.180 --> 08:15.300
among political persons, but still

08:15.300 --> 08:17.040
is an intriguing offer.

08:17.960 --> 08:18.960
There is one basic

08:18.960 --> 08:20.480
problem in the idea,

08:21.280 --> 08:22.980
I mean there are many, but one I think is

08:22.980 --> 08:25.020
particularly evident and strong, that

08:25.020 --> 08:27.340
this kind of formula presupposes

08:27.340 --> 08:29.220
a peaceful world.

08:29.840 --> 08:31.200
Whereas, as was said

08:31.200 --> 08:31.940
before,

08:33.480 --> 08:34.760
identity problem

08:34.760 --> 08:37.060
begin, as Achille said before,

08:37.060 --> 08:38.560
identity problem

08:38.560 --> 08:40.020
are connected

08:40.780 --> 08:43.340
almost always with hard times.

08:43.780 --> 08:45.080
They are caused by violence,

08:46.200 --> 08:47.560
by offence.

08:47.600 --> 08:49.260
I mean, as Martin

08:49.260 --> 08:51.080
Hassen has written, we have many

08:51.080 --> 08:52.940
identities. When radical

08:52.940 --> 08:54.920
identity comes out, it's because

08:54.920 --> 08:55.960
these many identities,

08:57.160 --> 08:59.160
at least part of them, are offended

08:59.160 --> 09:01.240
and humiliated. That's why

09:02.380 --> 09:03.060
we...

09:03.060 --> 09:05.180
And this means that

09:05.180 --> 09:07.620
liberal multiculturalism is very difficult

09:07.620 --> 09:09.040
because you assume

09:09.040 --> 09:11.340
a peaceful world, whereas

09:11.340 --> 09:12.880
radicalization of identity

09:12.880 --> 09:15.520
comes out in a very

09:15.520 --> 09:16.540
hard world.

09:17.400 --> 09:18.940
The second

09:18.940 --> 09:21.560
model we have in political philosophy

09:21.560 --> 09:23.560
is probably post-colonialism,

09:24.060 --> 09:25.120
which is more

09:25.120 --> 09:27.180
a bunch of different doctrines,

09:29.160 --> 09:31.180
but still as a kind of

09:32.020 --> 09:32.820
found soul.

09:33.540 --> 09:34.980
I think that

09:34.980 --> 09:37.320
post-colonialists have different problems.

09:37.840 --> 09:39.040
It's more apt

09:39.040 --> 09:40.840
to our times, but

09:41.840 --> 09:42.920
and I think

09:42.920 --> 09:44.980
it's a problem between the first level and the second

09:44.980 --> 09:47.380
level. The first level being the level

09:47.380 --> 09:48.800
of the object of

09:48.800 --> 09:51.180
post-colonialism, mainly what Achille calls

09:51.180 --> 09:52.400
epistemic injustice.

09:53.320 --> 09:55.040
On this side, I think post-colonialism

09:55.040 --> 09:56.760
is quite right. There has been an

09:56.760 --> 09:58.820
epistemic injustice and we should

09:58.820 --> 10:00.720
do something to understand each other,

10:00.720 --> 10:02.880
to not offend people continuing

10:02.880 --> 10:04.460
with the epistemic injustice.

10:06.100 --> 10:06.620
But I think

10:06.620 --> 10:08.820
post-colonialism has an enormous problem

10:08.820 --> 10:10.540
with the second level argument,

10:11.260 --> 10:12.740
which usually

10:12.740 --> 10:14.380
comes from post-modernism.

10:14.660 --> 10:16.980
This second Archimedean

10:16.980 --> 10:19.180
argument is an argument

10:19.180 --> 10:20.980
based on profound skepticism

10:21.260 --> 10:23.080
or reason. And I think that

10:23.080 --> 10:24.540
the second level argument,

10:24.800 --> 10:26.820
the meta-argument, cancels the

10:26.820 --> 10:28.680
possibility of the object

10:28.680 --> 10:30.820
of post-colonialism. So it's

10:30.820 --> 10:32.760
basically both models don't

10:32.760 --> 10:34.480
work. Of course I

10:34.480 --> 10:36.560
reduced my criticism to a few words, but

10:36.560 --> 10:38.780
it's what is possible in this short

10:38.780 --> 10:40.760
time. So I

10:40.760 --> 10:42.620
think we could work toward

10:42.620 --> 10:44.740
another model, which is

10:46.540 --> 10:46.860
a

10:46.860 --> 10:48.580
version of the Kimlisca model,

10:48.680 --> 10:50.680
but I think more modest in some

10:50.680 --> 10:52.680
way. It's not probably multiculturalism,

10:54.440 --> 10:54.900
it's not

10:54.900 --> 10:57.020
probably liberal multiculturalism,

10:57.020 --> 10:59.320
but what I call multicultural liberalism.

11:00.260 --> 11:01.180
It's not just

11:01.180 --> 11:03.240
for joking, it's not just

11:03.240 --> 11:05.180
a pun, but I think

11:05.180 --> 11:07.200
that the core of multicultural liberalism

11:07.620 --> 11:09.900
is constitutional pluralism.

11:10.660 --> 11:11.240
And this is

11:11.240 --> 11:11.920
the basis

